This article is for informational purposes only and does not, under any circumstances, constitute investment advice or a recommendation.

The crowdfunding platform Property Bridges announces the launch of a new investment opportunity in the residential market of Ireland. The project, promoted by the company Kilpep Development Limited, consists of granting a financing line for the development of a residential complex located at Ardmore Avenue, Bettystown, in County Meath.

The transaction is structured as a loan secured by a first-fixed-charge mortgage on the asset, offering an annual interest rate of 7.5% with a term of 13 months (and a minimum compliance period of 6 months). With a solid developer track record and a very advanced state of works, the project stands out for its mitigated risk profile and its strategic location in a high-demand area for Dublin workers.

Project Description: Sustainable Residential Development

The asset subject to the investment comprises a plot of 0.93 hectares (2.3 acres) that holds a valid planning license for the construction of 38 residential units. The design contemplates a typological mix of 2 one-bedroom homes, 22 two-bedroom homes and 14 three-bedroom homes.

A differential aspect of this development is the use of the ICF (Insulated Concrete Formwork) system, a modern poured-concrete construction method that guarantees superior airtightness and high thermal resistance. Thanks to this technology, all the homes will obtain an A2 BER energy rating, positioning them as highly efficient, low-consumption properties.

Currently, works on the site are progressing according to the planned schedule:

Investment Status and Capital Analysis

The financing request to Property Bridges amounts to €4,822,808, specifically intended to finance the construction of the first 28 houses of the complex. It is important to note that the developer has already made a significant investment effort:

The total market value once the 28 financed houses are completed (GDV) is estimated at €10,258,000. This places the loan-to-net-delivery-value ratio (LTNDV) at a solid 53.4%, which provides a comfortable safety margin for investors.

Location and Surroundings: The rise of Bettystown

Bettystown is a sought-after coastal town in the east of Meath, consolidated as a highly successful commuter town for those who work in Dublin. With a population of more than 15,600 inhabitants, it offers a wide range of services including cafés, restaurants and prestigious educational centers.

The project is located just 1.5 km from the town center and a short walk from Bettystown beach. Connectivity is one of its strong points, with quick access to the M1 motorway (facilitating arrival at Dublin Airport and the capital's center) and regular train services from Laytown station.

